-- Celtic Defeats Rangers 3-0 in Final Glasgow Derby of Season
-- B y   P e t e r - J o s e p h   H e g a r t y
-- 2012-04-29T13:59:57Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-29/celtic-defeats-rangers-3-0-in-final-glasgow-derby-of-season.html
 Celtic beat Glasgow city rival
Rangers 3-0 today in the final “Old Firm” game of the season.  Charlie Mulgrew gave Celtic the lead in the 17th minute and
Kris Commons made it 2-0 in the 31st.  Gary Hooper  got the third
nine minutes into the second half.  Celtic has already won the league title for the 43rd time.
Rangers are in administration, a form of protection from
creditors, after being engulfed by a financial crisis.  Celtic has 87 points, and second-place Rangers, deducted 10
points for going into administration, have 66.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Peter-Joseph Hegarty at 
 phegarty@bloomberg.net  